		<h1><a href="/blog/">A notch above a monkey</a> &raquo; Microformats and web clipboard</h1>
	</header>

	<section class="envelope">
		<article class="post">
			<header>
				<h1>Microformats and web clipboard</h1>
			</header>

			<footer>
				<ul>
					<li class="by">Written by: <a href="/">Marko Samastur</a></li>
					<li class="published">Published on: <time datetime="2006-03-09T14:16:06+00:00" pubdate>March 9, 2006</time></li>
					<li class="categories">Categories: <a href="http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/?cat=4" title="View all posts in Web" rel="category">Web</a></li>
					<li class="post-comments">Comments: <span>Comments Off</span></li>
				</ul>
			</footer>

			<div class="post-text">
				<p><a href="http://www.friedcellcollective.net/">Fry</a> gave <a href="http://web.zen.si/archives/2005/10/spletne-urice-2-mikroformati/">a talk</a> about microformats last October and some people back then were doubtful about their usefulness. Yesterday I read <a href="http://spaces.msn.com/rayozzie/Blog/cns!FB3017FBB9B2E142!285.entry">a post</a> by Ray Ozzie on the need for web clipboards and accompanying formats and my immediate thought was that microformats were perfect for this use.</p>
<p>Ray Ozzie talks about a need for easy interoperability and exchange of data between web sites and I believe most if not all of us who are working towards this goal agree that feeds (RSS or whatever) by themselves are not enough. Web clipboards seem to be a big step in right direction.</p>
<p>The post itself has since been updated with more information and a <a href="http://spaces.msn.com/editorial/rayozzie/demo/liveclip/liveclipsample/clipboardexample.html">great demo</a> how microformats could be used as a clipboard format for greater interoperability between different web services. You should check it out even if you don&#8217;t have doubts about the need for microformats.</p>
<p>I find it odd that these days I get more excited by stuff that&#8217;s coming out of Microsoft then out of Google.</p>
			</div>

